# Director / Head of Consulting

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 1 :

- Lead the overall growth strategy for the consulting practice, managing the P&L and ensuring profitability.
- Develop and execute go-to-market strategies to acquire new enterprise clients.
- Build and mentor a high-performing team of senior consultants and practice leaders.
- Act as the primary executive sponsor for key strategic accounts.

Skills:
Practice management, P&L ownership, Business development strategy, Executive leadership, Team mentorship.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 2 :

- Define the strategic vision for the financial services consulting vertical.
- Drive revenue growth through cross-selling and up-selling to existing banking clients.
- Oversee the delivery of large-scale digital transformation programs to ensure quality and value.
- Represent the firm at industry conferences and publish thought leadership.

Skills:
Strategic vision definition, Revenue growth strategy, Account expansion, Thought leadership, Delivery excellence.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 3 :

- Manage the operational efficiency of the consulting unit, including utilization and billability.
- Partner with the sales organization to shape complex consulting deals.
- Design and launch new service offerings to meet emerging market demands.
- Resolve critical escalations and maintain high client satisfaction scores (CSAT).

Skills:
Operational efficiency, Sales collaboration, Service offering design, Escalation management, Client satisfaction management.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 4 :

- Lead the organizational change management (OCM) practice.
- Develop proprietary change methodologies and toolkits for the firm.
- Advise C-suite executives on navigating cultural shifts during M&A.
- Commercialize OCM services and drive practice revenue.

Skills:
Change methodology design, Executive advisory, M&A cultural integration, Practice commercialization, Revenue generation.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 5 :

- Head the supply chain and operations consulting business.
- Drive thought leadership in Industry 4.0 and smart manufacturing.
- Manage senior relationships with COOs and Supply Chain Heads.
- Oversee the quality assurance of complex supply chain optimization projects.

Skills:
Supply chain strategy, Industry 4.0 awareness, C-level relationship management, Quality assurance, Operational excellence.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 6 :

- Build the cybersecurity risk advisory practice from the ground up.
- Define the service catalog for CISO advisory, compliance, and resilience.
- Recruit top talent to scale the team capabilities.
- Establish alliances with security technology vendors to drive joint go-to-market.

Skills:
Practice building, Talent acquisition, Vendor alliance management, Service catalog definition, Cybersecurity strategy.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Job Description 7 :

